          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/murf-ai-new-features"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Murf ships updates frequently, and a few recent additions genuinely improved my workflow. We keep a running list of ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "new Murf AI features",
            "marks": [
              "l4"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", but here are the ones I use most:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "AI Voice Agents & API",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Murf launched a blazing-fast text-to-speech API built for voice agents and automated systems. If you are building a chatbot, IVR system, or any product that needs real-time speech synthesis, this API delivers low-latency, natural-sounding output at scale. Over 10 million developers and businesses already use it.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "AI Dubbing",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Instant AI dubbing lets you translate and re-voice content into multiple languages while preserving the original speaker's tone and timing. I used this to localize a product demo from English to Spanish and Portuguese in under an hour. No freelance dubbing artists, no scheduling headaches.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Ultra-Realistic Voice Styles",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Murf now offers multiple style variations within a single voice. Think \"conversational,\" \"narration,\" \"newscaster,\" and \"empathetic\" — each one shifts the delivery in subtle but meaningful ways. For a healthcare explainer, I used the empathetic style, and the client said it matched the tone of their best human narrator.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Voice Cloning",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Upload samples of a specific voice, and Murf can create a digital clone that reads any script in that voice. Brands that want consistent audio identity across thousands of assets find this invaluable. It sounds like science fiction, but I tested it with a podcast host's recordings, and the clone was eerily accurate.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Collaboration & Multi-Editor Support",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Teams can now work inside the same project simultaneously. Comments, version history, and shared asset libraries keep everyone aligned. This eliminated the \"which version did you approve?\" back-and-forth that used to plague our production cycles.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l5",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/why-choose-murf-ai"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you want to see how Murf compares specifically to other AI voice tools, we put together a guide on ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "why choose Murf AI",
            "marks": [
              "l5"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " over alternatives.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tips & Best Ways to Get the Most Out of Murf AI",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "After generating hundreds of voiceovers, here are the practices that consistently produce the best results:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Write for the Ear, Not the Eye",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Spoken language reads differently than written text. Shorter sentences. Fewer clauses. When I rewrote a dense 400-word paragraph into three punchy sentences, the Murf output went from passable to genuinely engaging. Read your script aloud before pasting it in — if you stumble, the AI will too.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Use SSML-Style Pauses Strategically",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Murf lets you insert pauses of custom duration between words and sentences. I drop a 0.4-second pause before key points in presentations and a 0.2-second pause between list items. It mimics natural pacing and gives listeners time to absorb information. The difference between a rushed voiceover and a polished one often comes down to these micro-breaks.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Match Voice to Context",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Not every voice fits every project. A deep baritone might work for a cinematic trailer but feel off in a friendly SaaS onboarding video. I keep a shortlist of five voices I rotate depending on the use case:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Explainer videos:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Warm, mid-range, conversational tone",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
